# shebok.ai — Cursor Rules

## Project
Bangladesh-first AI healthcare navigator. WhatsApp triage + conversational booking + doctor portal.
Stack: Next.js · Supabase · n8n · Groq · Together.ai · BanglaBERT · BioBERT · ChromaDB/pgvector.

## TypeScript / Next.js
- TypeScript strict mode always. No `any` — use `unknown` + Zod narrowing.
- Next.js 14+ App Router. Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- Use `@/` import alias. Match existing shadcn/ui patterns in `apps/portal`.
- Validate all external JSON (LLM outputs, webhooks, DB writes) with Zod schemas before use.

## Database (Supabase)
- Never store raw phone numbers or NID — SHA-256 hash at ingestion only.
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` only in n8n workflows and Next.js server routes — never client bundles.
- All tables use RLS. Doctors query only their specialty + institution records.
- Use generated types from `apps/portal/src/types/database.types.ts` once schema exists.
- pgvector embeddings are 384-dim (S-PubMedBert-MS-MARCO).

## LLM Pipeline Rules
1. BanglaBERT: MEDICAL vs CHITCHAT only — not emergency detection.
2. Meditron-7B: outputs JSON `{ emergency_detected: boolean, primary_clinical_observation: string }`.
3. DeepSeek-R1: triage nurse persona (no diagnoses, no drug dosages). Strip `` blocks before patient text or DB insert.
4. BioBERT: runs ONLY after `triage_complete` — input is full conversation transcript, not single turns.
5. Malformed LLM output → schema validation gate → auto-retry once → deterministic fallback. Never write broken data.

## n8n Workflows
- PII scrub (SHA-256) before any external API call.
- Emergency branch terminates pipeline — no DeepSeek, no booking nodes.
- Conversation state in Supabase JSON buffer, 24hr TTL.

## Security
- No secrets in code, commits, or client-side env (`NEXT_PUBLIC_` only for anon-safe values).
- Patient text wrapped in delimiters before LLM calls (prompt injection guard).
- Open-weights models only in patient pipeline — no OpenAI/Anthropic for live triage.

## File layout
- `apps/portal/` — Next.js doctor portal
- `services/ml/` — BanglaBERT + BioBERT Flask endpoints
- `services/n8n/` — Docker compose for local n8n
- `.env.local` at repo root — single source of truth for local dev

## Style
- Minimal diffs. Reuse existing abstractions. No over-engineering.
- Comments only for non-obvious clinical or pipeline logic.
